def: To whip lightly or with a quick jerk; to flap; as, to flick ahorse; to flick the dirt from boots. Thackeray.

A certain tenure in tail special; an estate of inheritancegiven to a man his wife (the wife being of the blood of the donor),and descendible to the heirs of their two bodies begotten. [Obs.]Blackstone.
A female friend who attends on a bride at her wedding.
A genus of small European and American trees; the spindle tree.The bark is used as a cathartic.

Spurge, or bastard spurge, a genus of plants of many species,mostly shrubby, herbaceous succulents, affording an acrid, milkyjuice. Some of them are armed with thorns. Most of them yieldpowerful emetic and cathartic products.
Repairing, or tending to repair. Jer. Taylor.
A silver coin, and money of account, in the East Indies.

An organic base belonging to the phenylamines. It may beregarded as ammonia in which one hydrogen atom has been replaced bythe radical phenyl. It is a colorless, oily liquid, originallyobtained from indigo by distillation, but now largely manufacturedfrom coal tar or nitrobenzene as a base from which many brilliantdyes are made.
